The paper proposes a framework for large-scale question analysis using Bayesian deep learning methods, specifically partial variational auto-encoders. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with natural language processing (cs.CL) as it analyzes educational data. Additionally, the paper is related to education technology (cs.ED) as it focuses on analyzing educational resources. Finally, the paper may also be related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with analyzing images and questions related to them.
